56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.028d95c2-a91e-4c66-a3af-b5743d0cc73a.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.1d683232-e589-401b-bb7e-0a90762c50e2.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.3668167e-65b5-46ff-9a70-38cb83b5bfb1.description=
Clears the value of a context variable

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to clear

Responses\:
success - cleared the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, null];

Use * for all threshold - the value used to determine the response user - user account to use to connect to machine password - password for user account responses\: success - Measured values were below threshold. diagnosed - Measured Values were above threshold. failure - Something went wrong. 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.5bc6decf-3928-4d40-8780-e67ded60a16b.prompt=Enter a value for log 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.5d5018cc-a189-4488-a45e-03fd18d0fd42.prompt=Notification method 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.6200e8b9-b82b-4773-97a5-912d6fb82ce3.prompt=Notification option\: 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.6f32852f-af29-43ed-bc1b-d59d5fb85d80.prompt=delimiter? 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.76cf4d92-d87e-47ee-aed1-739f4c624c5f.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.cd1cb2fc-7770-499f-b832-4a71f18d63f0.prompt=Enter a value for age 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.defaa69f-a404-4fc3-855f-eb8da9ff9dfd.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.description=
Checks if a number of events in an event log exceeds a threshold, and recommends action if they do.
      
      inputs\:
threshold - A threshold to compare the measuredValue against..
Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic.
diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together.
recommended resolution - A recommendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold.
host - hostname or ip address of the machine you want to search against
log - the name of the Event Log to search (ex. Application or System or Security or *)
source - the source of the event
eventids - the eventid of the event
delimiter - a delimiter that separates eventids.
severity - (error, information, warning, *) the severity of the event.  Use * for all
message - the message text of the event (this input requires a regular expressions)
age - (value, *) the number of seconds old an event can be to be counted.  Use * for all
threshold - the value used to determine the response
username - user account to use to connect to machine
password - password for user account
notifyMethod - How you would like to be notified of problems that are found.
     
responses\:
success - Measured values were below threshold.
diagnosed - Measured Values were above threshold.
failure - Something went wrong.
56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.df12c9fb-eab5-4959-adb5-277c65b7b315.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifyData to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processin tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requireing authentication. password - The password for username. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 56fac8a8-c84f-4589-8789-308b42b67b2a.f1ba224c-289e-4974-b990-37642896bfcd.prompt=Enter a value for host
